			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-717992">
									

<p>As has been said, the concept (object we never built, whose intensity is gradually ratcheting up) is interesting but the effects leave a lot to be desired. Why would the Foundation bother causing mass insanity when it could make people vanish, or just freakin' shoot them?</p>
<p>Does this even need to be a weapon? What if, instead, it was a tool for some kind of weird terrain engineering, uprooting whole landscapes into Seussian parodies at high intensities? What if it were an amnesia ray, useful for controlling large-scale confidentiality breaches (and less <em>selective</em> at higher intensities, possibly even implanting memories that cause some [DATA EXPUNGED] when you crank it up to Keter)?</p>
<p>This could be really good; it just isn't <em>yet</em>.</p>

